//INSTRUCTIONS
//How to create a text
//================================
/*
  scr_text(str,type,x,y,portrait_sprite,portrait_image,str2,str3,str4,str5,str6,str7,str8,str9,id);
  
  'str' is the first message to be displayed.
  'type' is limitied to "Speech" , "Statement" , "Story" -- these change the draw style within the textbox.
  'x' is the upper-left x coordinate of the textbox.
  'y' is the upper-left y coordinate of the textbox.
  'portrait_sprite' accepts a sprite_index.
  'portrait_image' accepts integer values, and is the image_index.
  'str2' to 'str9' accept strings and are for additional messages.
  'id' is instance id of the object calling the script.
  
  IMPORTANT NOTE:
  Default script call: scr_text("This is a string.","Statement",0,0,"","","This is another string.","","","","","","","",id);
  Only input portrait_sprite and portrait_image if 'type' is "Speech".
*/
//================================

//Controlling text
//================================
/*
IMPORTANT NOTE: 
All effects can be inserted at desired locations within your message(s)(str to str10).

To change text-color:@Xstring@                   where 'X' is a one of the defined letter codes (see letter codes below), and 'string' is a portion within your message (str to str10).
To change portrait:&amp;sprite_index/image_index&amp;  
To insert an icon:^N                          where 'N' is the integer value for the image_index of sprite index s_text_icon.
To pause text:&lt;N&gt;                         where 'N' is an integer value, representing the amount of steps to wait.
To use shake effect:*N/PMwhere 'N' is the length of time, and 'P' is the shake magnitude.
To insert a sound:|sound_index/where 'sound_index' is the resource index of the track you want to play. NOTE: Sounds default to format: audio_play_sound(sound_index,2,false);
To insert a variable's data (GM2 EXCLUSIVE):((index,var/N               where 'index' is the object_index containing the desired variable, 'var' is the desired variable, and 'N' is the desired color code.
To move the text box:           ()x/y,spd/                  where 'x' is the value to add to the text box's current x-coord, 'y' is the value to add to the text box's current y-coord, and 'spd' is the speed --(max 10) a speed of 10 will move instantly.

To add a conditional:C(N,YN) or C(N,TF) or C(N,con1/con2/con3/con4/con5)
The N portion represents the variable to be changed within the calling instance.
For example, if N is 3, the calling instance must have a variable called conditional3 created.
When a choice is chosen, the appropriate conditionalN variable will be set to an integer value based on the choice.
For instance, using C(2,YN), and having the user choose option 'Yes', will set the variable conditional2 = 1 -- because the first option was chosen (conditional2 = 2 if 'No' was chosen).
For the 3rd form of using conditionals, C(N,con1,con2...conN), up to 5 user defined options may be created.

*/
